                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d542">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00 Revolutions/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Puerto Cortes</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wasson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Puerto Cortes</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-19T09:00:00-07:00"
                            >April 19, 1931—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Armed uprisings took place south and east of San Pedro last night. It is reported
                    that revolutionary forces are accompanied by General Ferrera.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wasson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
